WEBVTT

00:02.469 --> 00:03.604
<i>PREVIOUSLY</i>
<i>ON "DEVIOUS MAIDS"...</i>

00:03.604 --> 00:04.738
GO TO REHAB.
WHEN YOU GET BACK...

00:04.738 --> 00:06.740
I WILL BE HERE
WAITING FOR YOU.

00:06.740 --> 00:09.176
MORNING.
OH, CRAP.

00:09.176 --> 00:11.378
DAD SAYS YOU TWO ARE
GETTING BACK TOGETHER.

00:11.378 --> 00:12.513
YOUR FATHER'S CONFUSED.

00:12.513 --> 00:14.081
WE'RE GOING TO PARIS?

00:14.081 --> 00:15.182
YOU SAID YOU ALWAYS
WANTED TO SEE IT.

00:15.182 --> 00:16.350
SO, YOU'D RATHER BE
WITH JAVIER?

00:16.350 --> 00:17.518
I DON'T KNOW.

00:17.518 --> 00:20.220
SOMEONE IS WILLING
TO GIVE ME A KIDNEY?

00:20.220 --> 00:22.055
WHO IS THIS ANGEL?

00:22.055 --> 00:24.258
HE'S MARRIED TO YOUR MAID.

00:24.258 --> 00:25.359
I'M HIS LEGAL GUARDIAN.

00:25.359 --> 00:26.493
MR. KENNETH HAS
TAKEN BACK

00:26.493 --> 00:27.761
HIS POWER OF ATTORNEY.

00:27.761 --> 00:29.596
I AM GONNA SEE TO IT

00:29.596 --> 00:31.532
YOU ARE THROWN
OUT OF THIS COUNTRY.

00:31.532 --> 00:32.633
[ GUNSHOT ]

00:32.633 --> 00:34.201
OH, MY GOD!
YOU SHOT HIM!

00:34.201 --> 00:36.236
I HOPE YOU'RE NOT GONNA
SAY ANYTHING TO THE COPS.

00:36.236 --> 00:38.572
I ALREADY TOLD THE POLICE
EVERYTHING I KNOW.

00:38.572 --> 00:40.340
WE HAVE TO GET RID
OF VALENTINA.

00:40.340 --> 00:41.975
BEEN 15 YEARS
SINCE HE DIED.

00:41.975 --> 00:43.677
HAVE YOU FORGIVEN ME YET?

00:43.677 --> 00:45.345
YOU TOOK YOUR EYES
OFF OF HIM.

00:45.345 --> 00:46.613
YOU LET THAT CAR
PLOW RIGHT INTO HIM.

00:46.613 --> 00:48.215
MAYBE YOU <i>DID</i>
KILL SOMEONE.

00:48.215 --> 00:49.616
IT'S NOT WHAT YOU THINK.

00:49.616 --> 00:52.085
MAYBE SHE HAD SOME
PHYSICAL PROOF OF WHAT HE DID.

00:52.085 --> 00:53.353
DO YOU KNOW
WHERE SHE WAS STAYING?

00:53.353 --> 00:55.355
THIS SILVER KEY
ISN'T MINE.

00:55.355 --> 00:56.623
OPAL'S BANK.

01:00.127 --> 01:00.994
OH, MY GOD.

01:09.002 --> 01:11.505
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

01:11.505 --> 01:12.639
HEY. IT'S TIME.

01:12.639 --> 01:14.241
UH, I'LL BE RIGHT THERE.

01:14.241 --> 01:18.412
WHAT THE HELL WAS INSIDE
THAT SAFE DEPOSIT BOX?

01:18.412 --> 01:20.681
YOU'VE BEEN CRYING
FOR THE LAST TWO HOURS.

01:20.681 --> 01:22.082
I'LL TELL YOU LATER.

01:22.082 --> 01:23.617
TODAY IS ABOUT ROSIE.

01:29.456 --> 01:32.092
THIS IS SO NICE OF YOU GUYS,
TAKING ME OUT FOR LUNCH.

01:32.092 --> 01:33.760
WE THOUGHT YOU DESERVED
A NICE MEAL

01:33.760 --> 01:35.662
IN A FANCY RESTAURANT
FOR A CHANGE.

01:35.662 --> 01:37.431
YOU'VE BEEN THROUGH
SO MUCH.

01:37.431 --> 01:40.667
YOU KNOW, THIS COULD BE
MY LAST MEAL IN THIS COUNTRY.

01:40.667 --> 01:42.202
NO, I'M SURE
YOU'LL FIND A WAY

01:42.202 --> 01:43.236
TO CLEAR UP
YOUR IMMIGRATION PROBLEMS.

01:43.236 --> 01:44.338
HOW?

01:44.338 --> 01:45.505
THE HEARING IS
NEXT WEEK,

01:45.505 --> 01:47.341
AND REGGIE THREW AWAY
ALL OF MY DOCUMENTS.

01:47.341 --> 01:50.444
WELL, I GUESS WE JUST
HAVE TO HOPE FOR A MIRACLE.

01:54.615 --> 01:56.249
OH, NO!

01:56.249 --> 01:57.751
IT'S CLOSED.

01:57.751 --> 02:00.454
HMM. FOR A PRIVATE EVENT.
WONDER WHAT IT COULD BE.

02:00.454 --> 02:01.755
I'M CERTAINLY
CURIOUS.

02:01.755 --> 02:03.090
ME TOO.

02:03.090 --> 02:06.326
LET'S CRASH.
NICE!

02:06.326 --> 02:08.028
GIRLS!

02:08.028 --> 02:10.097
WE CAN'T DO THIS!

02:10.097 --> 02:11.431
[ SIGHS ]

02:13.967 --> 02:15.469
COME ON.

02:15.469 --> 02:18.005
WE'LL GET IN TROU...BLE.

02:23.343 --> 02:26.213
SPENCE?

02:26.213 --> 02:27.648
I THOUGHT
YOU WERE IN REHAB.

02:27.648 --> 02:29.383
OH, HE'S DONE
WITH ALL THAT.

02:29.383 --> 02:32.519
NOW HE HAS SOMETHING
HE WANTS TO ASK YOU.

02:41.228 --> 02:45.666
SO...IT'S JUST THE TWO OF US
FOR LUNCH?

02:45.666 --> 02:48.201
OH, NO. SOMEONE ELSE
WILL BE JOINING US.

02:48.201 --> 02:49.269
HEY, BUDDY.

02:50.470 --> 02:52.739
[ GASPS ] MIGUEL?

02:52.739 --> 02:55.075
YOU'RE SUPPOSED TO BE
WITH VALENTINA.

02:55.075 --> 02:57.210
OH, I COULDN'T DO THIS
WITHOUT HIM.

02:57.210 --> 02:58.745
DO WHAT?

03:07.287 --> 03:09.256
WAIT.

03:11.091 --> 03:16.063
THIS ISN'T JUST TO KEEP ME
FROM GETTING DEPORTED, IS IT?

03:16.063 --> 03:18.765
I LET YOU
GET AWAY FROM ME ONCE,

03:18.765 --> 03:22.202
AND I DON'T WANT THAT
TO HAPPEN AGAIN.

03:22.202 --> 03:24.037
[ CHUCKLES ]

03:26.073 --> 03:28.975
I CAN'T SEE ANYTHING.
WHAT'S GOING ON?

03:28.975 --> 03:30.544
SPENCE IS
DOWN ON ONE KNEE.

03:30.544 --> 03:32.279
IS ROSIE CRYING?

03:32.279 --> 03:33.613
BUCKETS.

03:33.613 --> 03:36.049
OH, MY GOD! HE'S PUTTING
THE RING ON HER FINGER!

03:36.049 --> 03:39.319
OH!
OH, YAY!

03:39.319 --> 03:41.121
MARRIAGE IS EXCITING,
ISN'T IT?

03:41.121 --> 03:43.590
YEAH.
YEAH, IT IS.

03:43.590 --> 03:46.093
NOW IF YOU'LL
BOTH EXCUSE ME,

03:46.093 --> 03:49.296
I HAVE TO GO TURN MY HUSBAND IN
TO THE POLICE.

04:12.119 --> 04:14.688
Adrian:
[ Echoing ] EVELYN?

04:14.688 --> 04:15.689
EVELYN?

04:17.124 --> 04:18.525
OH.

04:18.525 --> 04:20.327
I SAID, CAN YOU REMEMBER

04:20.327 --> 04:22.763
THE LAST TIME
WE WERE THIS HAPPY?

04:22.763 --> 04:24.631
NOT REALLY.

04:24.631 --> 04:27.434
WHY ARE YOU
SO SENTIMENTAL?

04:27.434 --> 04:29.469
IS IT
BECAUSE OF OUR ANNIVERSARY?

04:29.469 --> 04:30.470
OF COURSE.

04:30.470 --> 04:31.738
TOMORROW NIGHT,

04:31.738 --> 04:35.742
WE WILL HAVE BEEN MARRIED
FOR 25 YEARS.

04:35.742 --> 04:38.445
I KEEP WONDERING,
HOW IN GOD'S NAME DID WE MANAGE

04:38.445 --> 04:40.981
TO OUTLAST
SO MANY OTHER COUPLES?

04:40.981 --> 04:42.449
I THINK
IT'S OUR SENSE OF HUMOR.

04:42.449 --> 04:44.017
OH, I WAS GOING TO CREDIT

04:44.017 --> 04:46.086
OUR HIGH TOLERANCE
FOR ADULTERY AND PERVERSION.

04:46.086 --> 04:47.087
EITHER WAY...

04:47.087 --> 04:49.289
MR. POWELL!
MR. POWELL!

04:49.289 --> 04:51.224
AH!
SOMEONE HAS GOOD NEWS.

04:51.224 --> 04:54.060
I JUST GOT OFF THE PHONE
WITH BRUNO.

04:54.060 --> 04:55.262
I GOT
THE INTERNSHIP.

04:55.262 --> 04:57.497
OUTSTANDING!
CONGRATULATIONS.

04:57.497 --> 05:00.467
I'M FEELING EXCLUDED.
COULD SOMEONE FIX THAT?

05:00.467 --> 05:03.603
YOUR HUSBAND HELPED ME GET A JOB
WITH BRUNO DE LUCA.

05:03.603 --> 05:05.605
THE FASHION DESIGNER?

05:05.605 --> 05:08.475
MR. POWELL SENT HIM MY DRAWINGS,
AND MR. DE LUCA LOVED THEM.

05:08.475 --> 05:11.344
BRUNO OFFERED HER AN INTERNSHIP
IN MANHATTAN THIS SUMMER.

05:11.344 --> 05:13.180
AND MR. POWELL SAYS
I CAN STAY IN YOUR APARTMENT

05:13.180 --> 05:14.981
WHILE I'M THERE.

05:14.981 --> 05:19.019
SO, OUR MAID WILL BE LIVING
IN OUR $10 MILLION PENTHOUSE.

05:19.019 --> 05:21.488
THE NEIGHBORS
WILL BE THRILLED!

05:21.488 --> 05:25.292
OH, MR. POWELL,
THANK YOU SO MUCH.

05:27.093 --> 05:28.762
IT WAS MY PLEASURE.

05:28.762 --> 05:31.598
WELL, I HAVE TO
GET THE LAUNDRY DONE,

05:31.598 --> 05:34.100
SO [CHUCKLES]

05:34.100 --> 05:37.003
YOU AND VALENTINA SEEM
TO HAVE GROWN QUITE CLOSE.

05:38.038 --> 05:39.072
WHAT?

05:39.072 --> 05:41.208
I SAID
I'M GOING TO RODEO

05:41.208 --> 05:44.277
TO PICK UP
YOUR ANNIVERSARY GIFT.

05:44.277 --> 05:47.480
I CAN'T BELIEVE IT --
25 YEARS.

05:47.480 --> 05:49.115
HOW DID WE DO IT?

05:49.115 --> 05:52.419
IT CERTAINLY IS
A MYSTERY.

05:58.091 --> 06:00.160
Hagerty: WELL, THAT'S
QUITE A STORY, MRS. DEERING.

06:00.160 --> 06:02.062
HOW'D YOU
PIECE IT ALL TOGETHER?

06:02.062 --> 06:06.199
I FOUND THIS NEWSPAPER CLIPPING
YESTERDAY.

06:06.199 --> 06:08.602
AND THIS CLOTH.

06:08.602 --> 06:10.737
ACCORDING TO THE DATE
ON THE CLIPPING,

06:10.737 --> 06:12.305
THIS, UH,
TOOK PLACE IN '99.

06:12.305 --> 06:14.241
YEAH.
IT WAS A LONG TIME AGO.

06:14.241 --> 06:15.342
I DON'T GET IT.

06:15.342 --> 06:17.744
IF MR. DEERING WAS
RESPONSIBLE,

06:17.744 --> 06:19.212
WHY WOULD HE KEEP
ALL THIS?

06:19.212 --> 06:20.480
I FOUND THESE THINGS

06:20.480 --> 06:22.382
IN HIS HOUSEKEEPER'S
SAFE DEPOSIT BOX.

06:22.382 --> 06:25.285
I'M GUESSING SHE GOT THE CLOTH
FROM THE GRILLE OF HIS CAR.

06:25.285 --> 06:27.220
THAT'S WHAT SHE WAS USING
TO BLACKMAIL HIM.

06:27.220 --> 06:31.358
BUT SHE CAN'T CONFIRM THAT
BECAUSE SHE COMMITTED SUICIDE.

06:31.358 --> 06:35.695
UH...YEAH.

06:35.695 --> 06:37.364
SO, WHAT'S NEXT?

06:37.364 --> 06:39.099
DO YOU BRING NICK IN
FOR QUESTIONING?

06:39.099 --> 06:40.600
WHOA, WHOA.
SLOW DOWN.

06:40.600 --> 06:42.302
HAS YOUR HUSBAND CONFESSED
TO ANY OF THIS?

06:44.037 --> 06:45.338
NO.

06:45.338 --> 06:47.240
SO, ALL YOU HAVE
IN THE WAY OF EVIDENCE

06:47.240 --> 06:52.412
IS THIS SHRED OF CLOTH,
THIS OLD NEWSPAPER CLIPPING,

06:52.412 --> 06:54.247
AND YOUR SUSPICIONS?

06:54.247 --> 06:57.317
HE'S BEEN ACTING SUSPICIOUSLY
FOR MONTHS.

06:57.317 --> 06:59.352
I KNOW IN MY HEART
HE DID THIS,

06:59.352 --> 07:03.189
AND...I THINK IT WOULD BE WISE
TO ARREST HIM.

07:07.227 --> 07:09.529
MRS. DEERING,
I'M CURIOUS --

07:09.529 --> 07:11.298
HOW IS YOUR MARRIAGE?

07:15.001 --> 07:17.971
[ PIANO PLAYING ]

07:21.174 --> 07:23.576
[ Hispanic accent ]
CAN I BUY YOU ANOTHER?

07:25.612 --> 07:27.080
DON'T BOTHER.

07:27.080 --> 07:28.748
I HATE GETTING HIT ON.

07:28.748 --> 07:30.650
DOES IT HAPPEN A LOT?

07:30.650 --> 07:33.053
UM...LOOK AT ME.

07:33.053 --> 07:34.988
[ CHUCKLES ] LOOK AT YOU?
LOOK AT <i>ME.</i>

07:34.988 --> 07:36.389
YOU SHOULD BE FLATTERED.

07:36.389 --> 07:38.391
I'M THE HOTTEST GUY
IN HERE.

07:40.393 --> 07:42.095
THAT'S NOT SAYING MUCH.

07:42.095 --> 07:44.097
COME ON.
LET ME TALK TO YOU.

07:44.097 --> 07:46.199
YOU COULD LISTEN
TO MY SEXY ACCENT.

07:46.199 --> 07:49.035
IF I WANT TO HEAR A SEXY ACCENT,
I CAN TALK TO MYSELF.

07:49.035 --> 07:51.671
I'M SEBASTIEN.
AND YOU ARE...?

07:51.671 --> 07:53.473
NOT INTERESTED.

07:53.473 --> 07:55.075
I'D LIKE
TO CLOSE MY TAB.

07:55.075 --> 07:56.977
UH, NO, NO. NO.
YOU CAN'T GO.

07:56.977 --> 08:00.113
LOOK, IT'S NOT YOU.
I'M JUST IN A BAD MOOD.

08:00.113 --> 08:02.082
WHAT IS IT?

08:02.082 --> 08:03.483
TELL ME.

08:03.483 --> 08:05.485
OKAY.

08:05.485 --> 08:08.555
MY BEST FRIEND GOT ENGAGED TODAY
TO A GREAT GUY.

08:08.555 --> 08:10.623
NOW SHE'S GOT
EVERYTHING SHE EVER WANTED,

08:10.623 --> 08:13.360
AND IT MAKES ME THINK, WHEN IS
<i>MY</i> DREAM GONNA COME TRUE?

08:13.360 --> 08:15.362
WHAT IS YOUR DREAM?

08:15.362 --> 08:17.197
I WANT TO BE
A FAMOUS SINGER.

08:17.197 --> 08:18.398
OH.

08:18.398 --> 08:20.767
THAT'S, UH,
THAT'S A BIG DREAM.

08:20.767 --> 08:23.737
DON'T LOOK AT ME LIKE THAT.
I'M GOOD.

08:23.737 --> 08:26.306
I'VE BEEN WORKING
ON MY DEMO.

08:27.507 --> 08:30.076
CARMEN LUNA.

08:30.076 --> 08:31.644
HEY,
NOW I KNOW YOUR NAME.

08:31.644 --> 08:35.215
SOMEDAY, <i>EVERYBODY'S</i>
GONNA KNOW MY NAME.

08:35.215 --> 08:37.484
IT WAS NICE TO MEET YOU.

08:37.484 --> 08:38.718
REALLY?

08:38.718 --> 08:41.388
NOT YOU -- HIM.

08:45.658 --> 08:47.594
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS, DOOR OPENS ]

08:47.594 --> 08:49.629
WHERE THE HELL HAVE
YOU BEEN?
I'M SORRY.

08:49.629 --> 08:51.097
WE WERE SUPPOSED TO MEET
AN HOUR AGO,

08:51.097 --> 08:52.399
AND CARTER ISN'T RETURNING
ANY OF MY PHONE CALLS.

08:52.399 --> 08:54.534
TY, WE GOT TO TALK.

08:54.534 --> 08:56.236
FIRST, TELL ME --

08:56.236 --> 08:57.971
DID YOU DITCH THE GUNS?

08:57.971 --> 08:59.506
I DID.
BUT WE DON'T HAVE MUCH TIME.

08:59.506 --> 09:02.742
I-I JUST CAME
TO SAY GOODBYE.

09:02.742 --> 09:04.110
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

09:04.110 --> 09:05.979
I TOLD MY PARENTS
ABOUT THE ROBBERIES.

09:05.979 --> 09:07.580
WHAT?!
THEY FREAKED OUT AND SAID

09:07.580 --> 09:09.315
THAT THEY CAN'T PROTECT ME
IF I STAY HERE,

09:09.315 --> 09:10.984
SO THEY BOUGHT ME
A PLANE TICKET TO PERU.

09:10.984 --> 09:12.552
MY MOM'S GOT A COUSIN
OUT THERE.

09:12.552 --> 09:14.054
WHAT ABOUT ME AND CARTER?

09:14.054 --> 09:15.622
YOU'RE JUST GONNA LEAVE US
HOLDING THE BAG?

09:15.622 --> 09:17.757
CARTER LEFT FOR EUROPE
THIS MORNING.

09:17.757 --> 09:19.359
[ CHUCKLES ]

09:19.359 --> 09:20.727
YOU'RE LYING.

09:20.727 --> 09:22.128
WHEN HE TOLD HIS PARENTS,

09:22.128 --> 09:23.763
THEY DROVE HIM
STRAIGHT TO THE AIRPORT.

09:23.763 --> 09:25.498
DAMN IT!

09:25.498 --> 09:28.068
LOOK, I'M SORRY,
BUT I-I GOT TO GO PACK.

09:28.068 --> 09:31.004
I CAN'T BELIEVE
YOU GUYS ARE ABANDONING ME.

09:31.004 --> 09:32.372
WHAT DID YOU THINK
WOULD HAPPEN?

09:32.372 --> 09:34.107
FROM THE SECOND
YOU STARTED TALKING ABOUT

09:34.107 --> 09:35.208
GETTING RID OF VALENTINA.

09:35.208 --> 09:36.609
BUT IT MAKES SENSE.

09:36.609 --> 09:39.145
SHE'S THE ONLY ONE
WHO CAN TIE US TO THE ROBBERIES.

09:39.145 --> 09:41.681
WE KILLED ALEJANDRO
BY MISTAKE.

09:41.681 --> 09:43.216
WHAT YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT,

09:43.216 --> 09:45.185
WE'RE NOT GONNA BE
ANY PART OF IT.

09:45.185 --> 09:47.720
FINE.

09:47.720 --> 09:49.722
JUST GO, THEN.

09:53.293 --> 09:55.228
SERIOUSLY, DUDE,

09:55.228 --> 09:58.498
I THINK IT'S TIME YOU STARTED
TAKING YOUR MEDS AGAIN,

09:58.498 --> 10:00.533
'CAUSE THIS ISN'T YOU.

10:00.533 --> 10:02.635
[ DOOR OPENS, CLOSES ]

10:08.741 --> 10:10.210
HEY!

10:10.210 --> 10:11.344
YOU'RE NOT SUPPOSED TO BE
DRINKING

10:11.344 --> 10:12.745
WHEN YOU'RE
ON DIALYSIS.

10:12.745 --> 10:15.081
I WON'T BE MUCH LONGER.

10:15.081 --> 10:16.316
DRUM ROLL, PLEASE.

10:16.316 --> 10:18.685
I'M GETTING A NEW KIDNEY!

10:18.685 --> 10:21.254
[ GASPS ]
THEY FOUND A DONOR! OHH!

10:21.254 --> 10:24.757
THAT'S WHY
I'M CELEBRATING.

10:24.757 --> 10:27.060
I'M SENDING MY OLD KIDNEYS OFF
IN STYLE.

10:27.060 --> 10:28.761
SO, WHO IS IT?

10:28.761 --> 10:31.764
THAT'S THE BEST PART --
IT'S PABLO!

10:32.765 --> 10:35.135
MY PABLO'S
GIVING YOU A KIDNEY?

10:36.202 --> 10:37.604
HE DOESN'T EVEN LIKE
TO SHARE THE REMOTE.

10:37.604 --> 10:39.272
MAYBE HE'S CHANGED.

10:39.272 --> 10:41.474
MAYBE HE'S MORE GENEROUS
THAN YOU GIVE HIM CREDIT FOR.

10:41.474 --> 10:44.477
OR MAYBE HE'S TRYING
TO WIN ME BACK.

10:44.477 --> 10:47.480
EITHER WAY,
I GET A NEW KIDNEY!

10:47.480 --> 10:49.215
THAT'S THE PROBLEM.

10:49.215 --> 10:50.984
I'M NOT SURE
I WANT TO GET BACK WITH HIM.

10:50.984 --> 10:52.352
WHAT?!

10:52.352 --> 10:55.221
I MAY BE IN LOVE
WITH JAVIER.

10:55.221 --> 10:56.723
NO, NO.

10:56.723 --> 10:58.491
YOU LOVE PABLO.

10:58.491 --> 11:00.360
JAVIER IS JUST A CRUSH.

11:00.360 --> 11:01.561
I THINK
IT'S MORE THAN THAT.

11:01.561 --> 11:03.062
BUT YOU'RE NOT SURE.

11:03.062 --> 11:05.365
AND YOU HAVE A DAUGHTER
WITH PABLO

11:05.365 --> 11:07.367
AND A WONDERFUL HISTORY.

11:07.367 --> 11:08.601
HE CHEATED ON ME.

11:08.601 --> 11:10.603
AND NOW
HE'S SAVING MY LIFE.

11:10.603 --> 11:12.305
CUT THE MAN SOME SLACK.

11:12.305 --> 11:15.341
LOOK, PART OF ME WANTS
TO GET BACK TOGETHER WITH PABLO.

11:15.341 --> 11:17.110
WE HAD
A LOT OF GOOD YEARS.

11:17.110 --> 11:19.212
BUT I'M STILL SO ANGRY.

11:19.212 --> 11:21.714
WHAT IF I GO BACK TO HIM
AND IT DOESN'T WORK OUT?

11:21.714 --> 11:23.449
GOD, THIS IS COMPLICATED.

11:23.449 --> 11:25.552
THEN LET'S MAKE IT SIMPLE.

11:25.552 --> 11:27.153
DO YOU LOVE PABLO?

11:27.153 --> 11:29.088
YES.

11:29.088 --> 11:30.590
AND DO YOU LOVE <i>ME?</i>

11:30.590 --> 11:32.091
YES.

11:32.091 --> 11:34.727
THEN I THINK
YOU KNOW WHAT TO DO.

11:44.671 --> 11:47.473
HEY. HOW WAS SHOPPING?
DID YOU FIND A WEDDING DRESS?

11:47.473 --> 11:49.709
IT IS VERY BEAUTIFUL.

11:49.709 --> 11:52.378
BUT I THINK
IT'S TOO EXPENSIVE.

11:52.378 --> 11:55.448
I TOLD YOU --
MONEY'S NO OBJECT.

11:55.448 --> 11:58.218
I THINK MAYBE IT <i>IS.</i>

11:58.218 --> 12:00.253
YOUR CREDIT CARD
WAS DENIED.

12:00.253 --> 12:01.454
OH.

12:01.454 --> 12:02.689
WELL, I'LL TALK
TO THE BANK LATER.

12:02.689 --> 12:04.257
I'M SURE
WE CAN CLEAR THIS UP.

12:04.257 --> 12:06.059
GOOD.

12:06.059 --> 12:08.595
I WAS WORRIED WE MIGHT BE HAVING
MONEY PROBLEMS.

12:08.595 --> 12:10.663
HEY, GUYS.

12:10.663 --> 12:12.732
WHAT'S GOING ON?

12:13.733 --> 12:16.169
CARMEN,
DO WE HAVE ANY JUICE?

12:16.169 --> 12:17.503
SECOND SHELF
IN THE FRIDGE.

12:17.503 --> 12:19.172
IF YOU'RE GETTING UP,
I COULD USE A GLASS.

12:19.172 --> 12:23.176
ACTUALLY, I THOUGHT
YOU COULD BRING THE JUICE TO US.

12:23.176 --> 12:24.577
YOU'VE BEEN HERE
SIX HOURS.

12:24.577 --> 12:26.746
YOU ALREADY EXPECT ME
TO -- TO WAIT ON YOU?

12:26.746 --> 12:28.414
ISN'T THAT
WHAT YOU GET PAID FOR?

12:28.414 --> 12:30.083
NO.

12:30.083 --> 12:32.185
I GET PAID TO VACUUM, MOP,
AND WASH THE WINDOWS.

12:33.720 --> 12:35.421
THE WINDOWS ARE DIRTY.

12:37.090 --> 12:40.293
FINE.
I'LL GET YOU SOME JUICE.

12:40.293 --> 12:42.462
TO ANSWER YOUR QUESTION...

12:42.462 --> 12:45.498
THE DIVORCE
CLEANED ME OUT.

12:45.498 --> 12:47.066
AND NOW
THAT I'M NOT WORKING,

12:47.066 --> 12:48.701
YES, I'M A LITTLE STRAPPED
FOR CASH.

12:48.701 --> 12:50.169
WHY DIDN'T YOU
TELL ME THIS?

12:50.169 --> 12:51.571
BECAUSE I DIDN'T WANT YOU
TO WORRY.

12:51.571 --> 12:53.072
BUT I <i>DO</i> WORRY.

12:53.072 --> 12:55.174
WE'VE BEEN SPENDING SO MUCH
ON THIS WEDDING.

12:55.174 --> 12:57.477
AND WE SHOULD.
IT'S YOUR DAY.

12:57.477 --> 12:58.678
I WANT IT TO BE PERFECT.

12:58.678 --> 13:01.214
WELL, I WON'T BE ABLE
TO ENJOY IT

13:01.214 --> 13:03.182
KNOWING
THAT WE'RE GOING BROKE.

13:03.182 --> 13:06.185
WE'LL BE FINE.
I'LL GET ANOTHER JOB.

13:06.185 --> 13:07.754
UNTIL YOU DO,

13:07.754 --> 13:11.324
I THINK WE NEED
TO CUT BACK ON OUR SPENDING.

13:11.324 --> 13:13.760
OKAY. WHERE?

13:13.760 --> 13:16.496
DO WE NEED
SUCH A FANCY CAR?

13:16.496 --> 13:18.731
JUST PAID FOR IT.
IF I SOLD NOW, I'D LOSE MY ASS.

13:18.731 --> 13:20.099
WHAT ABOUT THE SAILBOAT?

13:20.099 --> 13:21.467
SOLD IT MONTHS AGO.

13:21.467 --> 13:23.603
THERE MUST BE <i>SOMETHING</i>
YOU SPEND MONEY ON

13:23.603 --> 13:25.038
WE DON'T REALLY NEED.

13:25.038 --> 13:27.674
OKAY.
HERE'S YOUR JUICE.

13:27.674 --> 13:29.442
AND DON'T BE ASKING
FOR A SNACK.

13:29.442 --> 13:30.743
I'M TAKING A BREAK.

13:30.743 --> 13:32.412
[ SCOFFS ]

13:40.186 --> 13:42.755
ZOILA.
WHAT A NICE SURPRISE.

13:42.755 --> 13:44.324
I HOPE
YOU'RE NOT BUSY.

13:44.324 --> 13:46.159
I HAVE
SOMETHING TO TELL YOU,

13:46.159 --> 13:49.228
AND I DIDN'T WANT TO DO IT
OVER THE PHONE.

13:49.228 --> 13:51.030
SOUNDS SERIOUS.

13:51.030 --> 13:52.031
IT IS.

13:54.033 --> 13:56.169
JAVI, I DON'T THINK
WE CAN GO TO PARIS.

13:56.169 --> 13:58.004
WHY NOT?

13:58.004 --> 13:59.706
THE OTHER NIGHT,

13:59.706 --> 14:02.075
WHEN VALENTINA WAS PULLED OVER
BY THE POLICE

14:02.075 --> 14:04.010
AND PABLO AND I WENT
TO HELP HER,

14:04.010 --> 14:05.712
ONE THING LED
TO ANOTHER, AND...

14:05.712 --> 14:07.613
[ SIGHS ]

14:07.613 --> 14:09.382
...WE HAD SEX.

14:12.752 --> 14:14.721
OH.

14:19.659 --> 14:22.428
I AM SO SORRY.

14:22.428 --> 14:24.731
WERE YOU DRUNK?

14:24.731 --> 14:26.199
I WISH.

14:26.199 --> 14:27.500
BUT NO.

14:32.004 --> 14:34.340
I AM VERY ANGRY.

14:34.340 --> 14:35.708
[ SIGHS ]

14:35.708 --> 14:38.578
BUT HE IS YOUR EX.

14:38.578 --> 14:41.581
YOU HAVE A LONG HISTORY
TOGETHER, AND...

14:41.581 --> 14:43.516
[ SIGHS ]

14:43.516 --> 14:46.586
...YOU OBVIOUSLY
FEEL GUILTY, SO...

14:46.586 --> 14:48.654
I THINK
I CAN FORGIVE YOU.

14:50.056 --> 14:52.158
WHY DO YOU HAVE TO BE
SO DAMN WONDERFUL?

14:53.426 --> 14:56.362
I COULD YELL IF YOU WANT,
BREAK SOME DISHES?

14:56.362 --> 14:59.031
AND NOW YOU'RE BEING ADORABLE.
STOP IT!

14:59.031 --> 15:01.033
THAT'S NOT EVEN
THE WORST PART!

15:01.033 --> 15:02.135
THERE'S MORE?

15:04.437 --> 15:06.706
I LOVE YOU.

15:06.706 --> 15:08.207
I DO.

15:08.207 --> 15:10.042
YOU'VE BEEN
NOTHING BUT AMAZING TO ME

15:10.042 --> 15:12.712
FROM THE MOMENT
I MET YOU.

15:12.712 --> 15:16.416
BUT PABLO AND I HAVE OVER
20 YEARS OF MARRIAGE TOGETHER,

15:16.416 --> 15:20.052
AND HE WANTS TO RECONCILE,
AND, FOR A LOT OF REASONS...

15:24.590 --> 15:27.160
...I THINK I HAVE TO GIVE HIM
A SECOND CHANCE.

15:28.761 --> 15:30.296
I SEE.

15:35.134 --> 15:37.303
DON'T HATE ME.

15:37.303 --> 15:39.172
[ SIGHS ]

15:39.172 --> 15:45.044
ALL I EVER WANTED
WAS FOR YOU TO BE HAPPY.

15:45.044 --> 15:48.448
I WAS JUST HOPING
IT WOULD BE WITH <i>ME.</i>

16:03.529 --> 16:05.264
YES, HI.

16:05.264 --> 16:07.066
I'M CALLING ABOUT THE LIMO
I ORDERED FOR THIS SUNDAY.

16:07.066 --> 16:09.702
I JUST GOT THE INVOICE.
YOU'RE CHARGING ME TOO MUCH.

16:09.702 --> 16:10.703
[ DOORBELL RINGS ]

16:10.703 --> 16:12.004
<i>DIOS MíO.</i>

16:12.004 --> 16:13.506
CAN YOU HOLD ON A SECOND?

16:15.675 --> 16:17.577
HEY. HOW ARE YOU?
BUSY.

16:17.577 --> 16:19.245
SORRY -- MY MOM AND I
CAN'T MAKE IT

16:19.245 --> 16:20.580
TO UNCLE SPENCE'S WEDDING,

16:20.580 --> 16:22.215
SO SHE WANTED ME
TO DROP OUR GIFT OFF.

16:22.215 --> 16:23.583
YEAH, THANKS.
PUT IT ON THE TABLE.

16:23.583 --> 16:26.319
YES. I'M STILL HERE.

16:26.319 --> 16:29.722
OKAY, THEN CAN YOU TELL ME
WHAT A CAR COSTS FOR FOUR HOURS?

16:29.722 --> 16:32.058
CAN I USE THE BATHROOM?
Yeah, yeah.

16:32.058 --> 16:33.759
WAIT --
IS THAT 7 OR 11?

16:33.759 --> 16:35.328
YOUR ACCENT IS SO THICK,

16:35.328 --> 16:37.363
I CAN'T UNDERSTAND
A WORD YOU'RE SAYING.

17:18.704 --> 17:20.706
CARMEN?

17:20.706 --> 17:22.975
WE HAVEN'T TALKED
IN A WHILE.

17:22.975 --> 17:24.377
[ SIGHS ]

17:24.377 --> 17:27.980
I WAS WONDERING, UH,
HOW IS YOUR SINGING GOING?

17:27.980 --> 17:30.116
NOT SO GOOD.

17:30.116 --> 17:32.118
MAYBE
WHEN I FINISH MY DEMO,

17:32.118 --> 17:34.120
BUT I HAVEN'T BEEN ABLE
TO GET BACK IN THE STUDIO.

17:34.120 --> 17:36.656
SO, WOULD IT HELP
IF YOU HAD MORE TIME

17:36.656 --> 17:38.257
TO FOCUS ON YOUR CAREER?

17:38.257 --> 17:39.625
SURE.

17:39.625 --> 17:42.128
THEN THAT'S
WHAT YOU SHOULD DO.

17:42.128 --> 17:45.264
SERIOUSLY?
I CAN TAKE SOME TIME OFF?

17:45.264 --> 17:46.666
TAKE AS MUCH TIME
AS YOU WANT.

17:46.666 --> 17:48.100
BUT WHO'S GONNA
CLEAN THE HOUSE?

17:48.100 --> 17:48.968
I WILL.

17:48.968 --> 17:50.570
THIS IS FANTASTIC!

17:50.570 --> 17:52.438
AND YOU'RE STILL GONNA
PAY ME?

17:52.438 --> 17:54.106
NO.

17:54.106 --> 17:56.609
WELL,
HOW DOES THAT WORK?

17:56.609 --> 17:59.545
THESE ARE
ALL GOOD QUESTIONS.

17:59.545 --> 18:00.980
LET ME GET BACK TO YOU.

18:00.980 --> 18:03.482
ROSIE?

18:03.482 --> 18:04.617
WHAT'S GOING ON?

18:08.087 --> 18:10.389
[ Voice breaking ] NOW,
YOU KNOW HOW MUCH I LOVE YOU.

18:10.389 --> 18:11.524
OH, MY GOD.

18:11.524 --> 18:13.159
YOU'RE FIRING ME?

18:13.159 --> 18:14.193
A LITTLE.

18:14.193 --> 18:15.661
WHY?

18:15.661 --> 18:17.263
[ SIGHS ]

18:17.263 --> 18:19.665
SPENCE LOST HIS JOB.

18:19.665 --> 18:21.334
WE CAN'T AFFORD YOU.

18:21.334 --> 18:23.402
WELL, YOU COULD IF YOU DIDN'T
LIVE IN THIS PALACE.

18:23.402 --> 18:24.637
YOU EXPECT US TO MOVE?

18:24.637 --> 18:26.105
WHAT, ARE YOU TOO GOOD
FOR A CONDO?

18:26.105 --> 18:27.273
CARMEN.

18:27.273 --> 18:28.407
AND IT WOULD BE
EASIER TO CLEAN.

18:28.407 --> 18:29.508
NO.

18:29.508 --> 18:31.677
I'M SORRY.
YOU HAVE TO GO.

18:31.677 --> 18:33.479
[ SIGHS ]

18:33.479 --> 18:36.015
OKAY. I GET IT.

18:36.015 --> 18:39.385
I'M NOT HAPPY ABOUT IT,
BUT I GET IT.

18:39.385 --> 18:41.654
OBVIOUSLY,
WE FEEL TERRIBLE ABOUT THIS,

18:41.654 --> 18:43.990
SO IF YOU CAN THINK
OF ANY WAY WE CAN HELP YOU,

18:43.990 --> 18:45.291
LET US KNOW.

18:45.291 --> 18:48.628
I'D LOVE
TO KEEP LIVING HERE.

18:49.695 --> 18:52.999
SO, GIVE IT SOME THOUGHT
AND GET BACK TO US.

18:57.370 --> 18:59.538
THANKS AGAIN
FOR LETTING ME MOVE BACK.

18:59.538 --> 19:01.040
THIS IS GONNA BE GREAT.

19:01.040 --> 19:02.141
I'M SURE IT WILL BE.

19:02.141 --> 19:03.542
JUST WATCH.

19:03.542 --> 19:06.612
THIS TIME AROUND, I'M GONNA BE
THE PERFECT HUSBAND.

19:06.612 --> 19:08.381
I'M NOT EXPECTING
PERFECTION.

19:08.381 --> 19:10.383
STILL,
I'M GONNA DO MY BEST

19:10.383 --> 19:12.985
TO MAKE YOU FORGET
ALL ABOUT JAVIER.

19:12.985 --> 19:14.620
[ DOORBELL RINGS ]

19:14.620 --> 19:16.188
I'LL GET THAT.

19:16.188 --> 19:18.524
YOU SETTLE IN,
AND THEN WE'LL MAKE DINNER.

19:18.524 --> 19:20.126
JUST LIKE OLD TIMES.

19:20.126 --> 19:21.694
[ SIGHS ]

19:24.764 --> 19:26.232
HELEN?

19:26.232 --> 19:27.400
IS PABLO HERE?

19:27.400 --> 19:29.268
HE LEFT THIS STUFF
AT MY PLACE.

19:29.268 --> 19:30.503
I'LL GET HIM.

19:30.503 --> 19:32.505
UH, DON'T BOTHER.
JUST GIVE IT TO HIM?

19:32.505 --> 19:34.006
OF COURSE.

19:34.006 --> 19:35.374
AND FOR WHAT IT'S WORTH,

19:35.374 --> 19:37.410
I'M REALLY SORRY
ABOUT EVERYTHING.

19:37.410 --> 19:39.045
WHAT EVERYTHING?

19:39.045 --> 19:41.113
I MEAN,
I'M SURE IT WAS DIFFICULT

19:41.113 --> 19:43.149
TO HAVE PABLO LEAVE
LIKE HE DID.

19:43.149 --> 19:45.518
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT HE'S BEEN TELLING YOU,

19:45.518 --> 19:47.086
BUT <i>I</i> BROKE UP WITH <i>HIM.</i>

19:47.086 --> 19:49.455
<i>YOU</i> BROKE UP WITH <i>HIM?</i>

19:49.455 --> 19:50.990
OVER A MONTH AGO.

19:50.990 --> 19:54.260
I COULDN'T TAKE THAT LYING BUM
ONE MORE DAY.

19:54.260 --> 19:58.197
TRUTH IS,
I HOPE HE DIES IN A GUTTER.

19:59.398 --> 20:02.468
I'LL TELL HIM
YOU STOPPED BY.

20:07.106 --> 20:08.340
WHO WAS THAT?

20:08.340 --> 20:10.242
THAT WAS HELEN.

20:10.242 --> 20:13.612
SHE...WANTED TO DROP OFF
YOUR STUFF.

20:13.612 --> 20:15.748
OH.

20:15.748 --> 20:18.150
DID SHE HAVE ANYTHING
INTERESTING TO SAY?

20:18.150 --> 20:20.219
SHE SURE DID.

20:21.387 --> 20:22.621
OH, GEEZ.

20:22.621 --> 20:25.124
NO, IT WAS GOOD.

20:25.124 --> 20:26.258
GREAT, EVEN.

20:26.258 --> 20:27.560
REALLY?

20:27.560 --> 20:29.662
'CAUSE I-I-I WOULD HATE
FOR YOU TO THINK

20:29.662 --> 20:33.399
THAT I CAME BACK JUST BECAUSE
I H-HAD NOWHERE ELSE TO GO.

20:33.399 --> 20:35.401
ARE YOU SURE
YOU'RE NOT ANGRY?

20:35.401 --> 20:39.505
WHAT I AM, PABLO,
IS RELIEVED.

20:42.508 --> 20:43.676
GOODBYE.

20:49.749 --> 20:51.684
ZOILA?

20:51.684 --> 20:53.252
I'M AN IDIOT.

21:07.399 --> 21:09.401
I KNOW WHAT YOU DID.

21:11.971 --> 21:14.006
AND WE NEED TO TALK.

21:16.075 --> 21:17.476
[ SIGHS SHAKILY ]

21:17.476 --> 21:20.446
WHAT I DON'T GET IS
HOW YOU COULD LIVE WITH YOURSELF

21:20.446 --> 21:21.514
ALL THESE YEARS.

21:21.514 --> 21:22.681
IT WAS AN ACCIDENT.

21:22.681 --> 21:24.250
BUT YOU LEFT!
YOU DROVE OFF!

21:24.250 --> 21:25.384
YOU THINK
I DON'T HATE MYSELF?

21:25.384 --> 21:28.087
NOT ENOUGH,
FROM WHERE I'M STANDING.

21:28.087 --> 21:31.991
I SPENT 15 YEARS SHUTTING MYSELF
OFF FROM THE WORLD.

21:31.991 --> 21:33.993
I WAS SO DISGUSTED
BY WHAT I'D DONE.

21:33.993 --> 21:36.295
I KNEW
I DIDN'T DESERVE TO BE HAPPY.

21:38.164 --> 21:39.532
BUT THEN I MET YOU.

21:39.532 --> 21:43.102
AND IF YOU HAD TOLD ME
THE TRUTH, TRUSTED ME...

21:43.102 --> 21:45.971
I WAS SCARED
OF LOSING YOU.

21:45.971 --> 21:48.674
AND I HAVE.

21:48.674 --> 21:50.109
I HAVE NOTHING NOW.

21:50.109 --> 21:51.577
NO! NO!

21:51.577 --> 21:54.113
I WILL NOT ALLOW YOU TO
SIT THERE AND PLAY THE VICTIM.

21:54.113 --> 21:56.615
WHAT YOU DID THAT DAY
SET OFF A CHAIN OF EVENTS

21:56.615 --> 22:00.519
THAT ALSO COST DAHLIA AND OPAL
THEIR LIVES.

22:00.519 --> 22:02.555
GOD, NICK!

22:02.555 --> 22:06.392
CAN YOU NOT SEE
THE BLOOD ON YOUR HANDS?

22:06.392 --> 22:08.294
[ SIGHS SHAKILY ]

22:11.664 --> 22:12.698
WHAT DO YOU NEED ME
TO DO?

22:14.366 --> 22:16.969
ULTIMATELY, I NEED YOU
TO GO TO THE POLICE.

22:18.971 --> 22:20.172
"ULTIMATELY"?

22:20.172 --> 22:22.007
FIRST, YOU MUST GO
TO THE POWELLS

22:22.007 --> 22:23.442
AND TELL THEM THE TRUTH.

22:23.442 --> 22:25.377
NO.

22:25.377 --> 22:27.246
I CAN'T FACE THEM.

22:27.246 --> 22:29.014
YOU HAVE TO.

22:29.014 --> 22:33.319
[ Voice breaking ] THEY NEED
TO KNOW WHO KILLED THEIR SON.

22:42.728 --> 22:44.563
HOW WAS DIALYSIS?

22:44.563 --> 22:48.133
THE DOCTOR SAID
THAT I LOOKED TOO THIN,

22:48.133 --> 22:50.236
AND HE DIDN'T MEAN IT
AS A COMPLIMENT.

22:50.236 --> 22:51.637
BUT IT WAS NICE TO HEAR.

22:51.637 --> 22:54.240
YOU'LL BE OKAY ONCE YOU HAVE
THE TRANSPLANT SURGERY.

22:54.240 --> 22:55.741
HAVE THEY SCHEDULED THAT
YET?

22:57.009 --> 22:58.344
NO.

22:59.745 --> 23:01.413
AND THEY'RE NOT GOING TO.

23:01.413 --> 23:03.249
WHAT?

23:05.017 --> 23:09.355
IT SEEMS PABLO WON'T BE
GIVING ME A KIDNEY AFTER ALL.

23:09.355 --> 23:10.656
BUT HE PROMISED!

23:10.656 --> 23:14.627
HE WAS JUST TRYING
TO WIN ZOILA BACK.

23:14.627 --> 23:17.997
AND NOW THAT SHE'S DECIDED
TO BE WITH JAVIER,

23:17.997 --> 23:19.431
HE CHANGED HIS MIND.

23:19.431 --> 23:21.533
DOESN'T SHE REALIZE
HOW SICK YOU ARE?

23:21.533 --> 23:23.302
IT'S NOT HER FAULT.

23:23.302 --> 23:26.272
IT'S JUST...
THE WAY IT IS.

23:26.272 --> 23:29.508
WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO?

23:29.508 --> 23:32.511
I DON'T KNOW.

23:32.511 --> 23:35.180
AREN'T YOU SCARED?

23:37.750 --> 23:41.420
I'M TERRIFIED.

23:41.420 --> 23:43.355
[ NOTES PLAY ]

23:45.457 --> 23:47.126
ROSIE, YOU'RE HERE.
COME HERE.

23:47.126 --> 23:48.360
I WANT YOU TO MEET

23:48.360 --> 23:51.363
THE ONE AND ONLY
MICHAEL FEINSTEIN.

23:52.598 --> 23:54.133
OKAY.

23:54.133 --> 23:55.234
HE'S KIND OF FAMOUS.

23:55.234 --> 23:57.002
WELL, NOT KIND OF.

23:57.002 --> 23:59.405
I'VE BEEN NOMINATED FOR A GRAMMY
FIVE TIMES.

23:59.405 --> 24:02.007
WOW!

24:02.007 --> 24:03.642
HOW MANY DID YOU WIN?

24:05.077 --> 24:06.979
I DON'T LIKE
TO TALK ABOUT AWARDS.

24:06.979 --> 24:08.380
HE'S AGREED
TO SING AT OUR WEDDING.

24:08.380 --> 24:10.349
WHAT A WONDERFUL GIFT.

24:10.349 --> 24:11.583
GIFT?

24:11.583 --> 24:14.553
I NEED
TO SPEAK TO MY FIANCéE.

24:16.388 --> 24:19.258
YOU'RE PAYING HIM
TO SING AT OUR WEDDING?

24:19.258 --> 24:20.559
WHAT WILL THAT COST?

24:20.559 --> 24:22.027
CAN WE NOT ARGUE
ABOUT MONEY RIGHT NOW?

24:22.027 --> 24:23.495
'CAUSE IT KIND OF
UPSETS ME.

24:23.495 --> 24:25.130
IT WILL UPSET ME
IF WE GO BROKE!

24:25.130 --> 24:27.533
RELAX.
I WILL GET WORK SOON.

24:27.533 --> 24:28.534
BUT WHAT IF YOU DON'T?

24:28.534 --> 24:30.102
ROSIE, I AM SORRY,

24:30.102 --> 24:32.371
BUT I REFUSE TO FREAK OUT
ABOUT STUFF LIKE THIS.

24:32.371 --> 24:33.739
THAT'S BECAUSE YOU DON'T KNOW
WHAT IT FEELS LIKE

24:33.739 --> 24:35.341
TO GROW UP WITHOUT MONEY.

24:35.341 --> 24:38.510
OKAY. I'LL -- I'LL TALK
TO MICHAEL ABOUT A DISCOUNT.

24:38.510 --> 24:42.047
I DON'T DO HEAVY METAL
OR DISCOUNTS.

24:46.185 --> 24:48.721
AND WHILE I'M DOING
MY INTERNSHIP IN NEW YORK,

24:48.721 --> 24:51.690
THE POWELLS ARE GONNA LET ME
LIVE IN THEIR APARTMENT.

24:51.690 --> 24:53.258
ISN'T THAT AMAZING?

24:53.258 --> 24:55.127
THAT'S GREAT NEWS, VAL.
COME HERE.

24:55.127 --> 24:57.062
[ CHUCKLES ]

24:57.062 --> 25:01.133
WELL, IT DOESN'T JUST HAVE TO BE
GREAT NEWS FOR <i>ME.</i>

25:01.133 --> 25:03.168
I THOUGHT
MAYBE YOU COULD COME WITH ME.

25:03.168 --> 25:05.537
WOULDN'T THAT BE FUN?
THE TWO OF US IN THE BIG APPLE.

25:05.537 --> 25:08.440
[ CHUCKLES ]
THAT SOUNDS AMAZING.

25:09.975 --> 25:11.377
WHAT'S WRONG?

25:11.377 --> 25:13.979
MY MOM IS REALLY SICK,

25:13.979 --> 25:16.215
AND YOUR DAD CHANGED HIS MIND
ABOUT GIVING HER HIS KIDNEY.

25:16.215 --> 25:19.251
[ SIGHS ]
I KNOW. HE TOLD ME.

25:19.251 --> 25:20.986
I'M SO SORRY.

25:20.986 --> 25:23.155
DON'T SUPPOSE YOU COULD ASK HIM
TO RECONSIDER?

25:23.155 --> 25:26.692
I CAN'T.
IT'S GOT TO BE <i>HIS</i> DECISION.

25:26.692 --> 25:28.460
THAT'S WHAT I FIGURED.

25:30.529 --> 25:32.064
ANYWAY, LOOK.

25:32.064 --> 25:35.634
AS MUCH AS I WOULD LIKE
TO BE WITH YOU,

25:35.634 --> 25:38.003
NOW IS JUST NOT A GOOD TIME
FOR ME TO LEAVE L.A.

25:38.003 --> 25:41.273
I GET IT.

25:41.273 --> 25:43.409
BUT I'LL PICK YOU UP
FOR ROSIE'S WEDDING TOMORROW?

25:43.409 --> 25:45.744
I'LL BE READY AT 9:00.

25:48.680 --> 25:50.482
VAL.

25:54.253 --> 25:55.988
WHY CAN'T WE
CATCH A BREAK?

25:55.988 --> 25:58.524
I DON'T KNOW.

26:02.661 --> 26:03.996
[ TELEPHONE RINGS ]

26:03.996 --> 26:04.997
[ TELEPHONE BEEPS ]

26:04.997 --> 26:06.165
HELLO?

26:06.165 --> 26:07.399
TY: Hi.
I'm calling for Valentina.

26:07.399 --> 26:08.467
Is she there?

26:08.467 --> 26:09.635
NO, I'M SORRY.
SHE'S NOT.

26:09.635 --> 26:11.170
Well,
I'm trying to find her.

26:11.170 --> 26:12.504
Do you know
where she might be?

26:12.504 --> 26:14.306
NOT RIGHT NOW.
WHO IS THIS?

26:14.306 --> 26:17.509
THIS IS HER FRIEND,
UH...SAM.

26:17.509 --> 26:19.511
Well, when I see her,
I'll tell her you called.

26:19.511 --> 26:21.513
YOU KNOW WHAT?
NEVER MIND.

26:21.513 --> 26:24.983
I'LL TRACK HER DOWN
EVENTUALLY.

26:24.983 --> 26:26.652
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

26:29.521 --> 26:32.257
[ PIANO MUSIC PLAYS ]

26:32.257 --> 26:34.059
[ SIGHS ]

26:35.761 --> 26:37.262
HEY.

26:37.262 --> 26:39.131
I LISTENED TO YOUR CD.

26:39.131 --> 26:40.666
HELLO, SEBASTIEN.

26:40.666 --> 26:43.502
YOU SING AS GOOD AS YOU LOOK,
AND YOU LOOK AS GOOD AS ME,

26:43.502 --> 26:46.238
WHICH MEANS
YOU ARE FANTASTIC.

26:46.238 --> 26:47.573
I'M GLAD YOU LIKED IT,

26:47.573 --> 26:51.977
BUT I'M -- I'M NOT IN THE MOOD
TO JOKE AROUND.

26:51.977 --> 26:54.580
WHY ARE YOU SO SAD?

26:54.580 --> 26:56.115
I GOT FIRED TODAY.

26:56.115 --> 26:57.983
THEN PLEASE --
LET ME BUY YOU A DRINK.

26:57.983 --> 27:00.285
DON'T GET ME WRONG --
I HATED MY JOB,

27:00.285 --> 27:01.720
BUT IT PAID THE BILLS.

27:01.720 --> 27:03.522
SO NOW I HAVE TO GET A NEW JOB,
WHICH I'LL HATE

27:03.522 --> 27:07.126
BECAUSE IT STILL WON'T BE
WHAT I WANT TO DO WITH MY LIFE.

27:07.126 --> 27:10.429
BUT WHAT IF I NEVER GET TO HAVE
THE LIFE I WANT?

27:10.429 --> 27:12.397
NOT EVERYBODY
GETS TO BE A STAR,

27:12.397 --> 27:15.234
SO SHOULD I JUST GIVE UP NOW
AND DO SOMETHING ELSE?

27:15.234 --> 27:17.970
BUT HOW CAN I DO THAT
IF MUSIC IS ALL I CARE ABOUT?

27:17.970 --> 27:20.706
IT'S MY LOVE,
MY PASSION.

27:20.706 --> 27:24.476
WELL, MAKE SURE TO SAY THAT
IN THE MEETING.

27:24.476 --> 27:25.444
HUH?

27:25.444 --> 27:26.645
I HAPPEN TO KNOW

27:26.645 --> 27:29.114
THE HEAD OF TALENT
AT DISCERNA RECORDS.

27:29.114 --> 27:31.650
I GAVE HER YOUR CD.

27:31.650 --> 27:33.485
SHE WANTS TO MEET YOU.

27:33.485 --> 27:35.487
ARE YOU SERIOUS?

27:35.487 --> 27:36.989
YEAH.

27:36.989 --> 27:38.090
[ CHUCKLES ]

27:40.092 --> 27:41.126
WAIT.

27:42.261 --> 27:45.764
YOU DIDN'T HELP ME JUST TO
GET ME INTO BED, DID YOU?

27:45.764 --> 27:47.432
NO.

27:47.432 --> 27:49.701
UH, I HELPED YOU BECAUSE
I THINK YOU CAN REALLY SING.

27:49.701 --> 27:54.039
THE DRINK I JUST BOUGHT YOU --
<i>THAT</i> WAS TO GET YOU INTO BED.

27:55.007 --> 27:56.408
[ CHUCKLES ]

27:56.408 --> 27:58.410
Adrian: WHAT IS THIS?

27:58.410 --> 28:01.113
IT'S A PRE-CLASSIC
MAYAN DAGGER.

28:01.113 --> 28:03.048
IT'S MAGNIFICENT.

28:03.048 --> 28:04.383
WHAT DID THEY USE IT FOR?

28:04.383 --> 28:07.452
I'M NOT SURE --
LOOTING, PILLAGING.

28:07.452 --> 28:09.755
MAYBE THEY EVEN
SACRIFICED VIRGINS WITH IT.

28:09.755 --> 28:11.757
GOD,
YOU KNOW ME SO WELL.

28:11.757 --> 28:13.525
WHAT DO YOU THINK
OF <i>YOUR</i> GIFT?

28:13.525 --> 28:15.627
IT'S LOVELY.

28:15.627 --> 28:17.696
THE INSCRIPTION'S
VERY SWEET.

28:17.696 --> 28:20.365
THAT'S IT?
THAT'S ALL I GET?

28:20.365 --> 28:22.167
I DON'T WANT TO FIGHT
ON OUR ANNIVERSARY.

28:22.167 --> 28:24.536
I'M NOT TRYING TO START A FIGHT.
I WAS ASKING A QUESTION.

28:24.536 --> 28:26.104
IT'S JUST,
EVERY TIME I THINK

28:26.104 --> 28:27.639
THINGS ARE GONNA GET BETTER
BETWEEN US,

28:27.639 --> 28:29.141
YOU GO BACK
TO YOUR OLD WAYS.

28:29.141 --> 28:30.642
MY OLD WAYS?

28:30.642 --> 28:34.446
I'M TALKING ABOUT VALENTINA.
IT IS FLORA ALL OVER AGAIN.

28:34.446 --> 28:35.614
THAT'S ABSURD!

28:35.614 --> 28:37.616
I THINK OF VALENTINA
AS A DAUGHTER.

28:37.616 --> 28:39.551
OEDIPUS WOULD BE SO PROUD.

28:39.551 --> 28:41.119
YOU HAVE A LOT OF NERVE,

28:41.119 --> 28:43.121
GIVEN YOUR RECENT ROMPS
WITH THE HELP.

28:43.121 --> 28:45.390
YES,
I HAD AN AFFAIR WITH TONY.

28:45.390 --> 28:47.059
<i>ONE</i> INDISCRETION

28:47.059 --> 28:49.695
COMPARED TO THE DOZENS OF WHORES
YOU HAVE SUPPORTED.

28:49.695 --> 28:51.263
MY INFIDELITIES WERE
THE RESULT

28:51.263 --> 28:53.031
OF AN UNDERSTANDING
YOU AGREED TO.

28:53.031 --> 28:55.000
WHAT CHOICE DID I HAVE?
YOU WERE GONNA LEAVE ME.

28:55.000 --> 28:57.035
DIDN'T I HAVE THE RIGHT
TO BE ANGRY?

28:57.035 --> 28:59.104
I TOOK MY EYES OFF BARRETT
FOR 10 SECONDS.

28:59.104 --> 29:00.606
IT'S NOT MY FAULT
HE'S DEAD.

29:00.606 --> 29:02.608
YOU HAVE MADE THIS
INTO AN ARGUMENT ABOUT OUR SON,

29:02.608 --> 29:04.509
AND THIS IS NOT ABOUT HIM.

29:04.509 --> 29:06.278
WHO ARE YOU KIDDING?
IT'S <i>ALWAYS</i> ABOUT OUR SON.

29:10.349 --> 29:14.286
MAYBE YOU AND I SHOULD JUST STOP
TRYING TO BE HAPPY.

29:14.286 --> 29:16.655
IT'S ALWAYS
SUCH A DISAPPOINTMENT.

29:26.265 --> 29:28.133
HEY.
WHERE YOU GOING?

29:28.133 --> 29:30.068
MY BEST FRIEND IS
GETTING MARRIED IN 16 HOURS.

29:30.068 --> 29:31.970
I HAVE TO HELP HER GET READY
FOR THE WEDDING.

29:31.970 --> 29:34.473
WELL, I HAD A GREAT TIME
LAST NIGHT.

29:34.473 --> 29:36.375
NO, <i>I</i> HAD A GREAT TIME.

29:36.375 --> 29:39.511
YOU HAD A <i>FANTASTIC</i> TIME.

29:39.511 --> 29:41.380
THIS IS TRUE.

29:41.380 --> 29:43.415
SO, OBVIOUSLY,
I WANT TO SEE YOU AGAIN.

29:43.415 --> 29:45.350
I THINK
WE CAN ARRANGE THAT.

29:52.424 --> 29:54.226
I LIKE YOU.

29:57.162 --> 29:59.731
WHICH IS
WHY I NEED TO BE HONEST.

29:59.731 --> 30:01.533
OKAY.

30:01.533 --> 30:04.102
YOU KNOW THAT MUSIC EXECUTIVE
I TOLD YOU ABOUT?

30:04.102 --> 30:06.238
GREAT. HERE IT COMES.

30:06.238 --> 30:08.006
THERE'S NO MEETING,
RIGHT?

30:08.006 --> 30:09.741
OH, SURE,
THERE'S A MEETING.

30:09.741 --> 30:12.010
THANK GOD. [ CHUCKLES ]
YOU HAD ME WORRIED.

30:12.010 --> 30:13.412
NO,
YOU'RE DEFINITELY MEETING

30:13.412 --> 30:15.480
WITH THE HEAD OF TALENT
FOR DISCERNA RECORDS.

30:15.480 --> 30:17.516
OKAY.

30:17.516 --> 30:20.385
THE PROBLEM IS...

30:20.385 --> 30:22.187
SHE'S MY WIFE.

30:24.122 --> 30:25.090
[ SIGHS ]

30:30.529 --> 30:32.030
Marisol: THANK YOU FOR SEEING US
ON SUCH SHORT NOTICE.

30:32.030 --> 30:34.132
I HOPE WE WEREN'T INTERRUPTING
ANYTHING IMPORTANT.

30:34.132 --> 30:37.402
WE WERE CELEBRATING
OUR ANNIVERSARY, SO...NO.

30:39.237 --> 30:43.375
BEFORE WE GET INTO YOUR REASON
FOR THIS UNEXPECTED VISIT,

30:43.375 --> 30:44.710
MAY I SAY SOMETHING?

30:46.311 --> 30:48.246
SURE.

30:48.246 --> 30:49.514
ADRIAN AND I HAVE BEEN

30:49.514 --> 30:51.750
A LITTLE BIT CROSS WITH YOU,
NICHOLAS.

30:51.750 --> 30:53.251
CROSS?

30:53.251 --> 30:54.586
YOU AND DAHLIA WERE
OUR DEAR FRIENDS.

30:54.586 --> 30:56.021
WE SPENT
EVERY WEEKEND TOGETHER.

30:56.021 --> 30:57.122
AND VACATIONS.

30:57.122 --> 30:58.390
AND THEN ONE DAY,

30:58.390 --> 31:00.192
YOU JUST STOPPED
RETURNING OUR PHONE CALLS.

31:00.192 --> 31:03.061
NOW, IF WE DID SOMETHING WRONG
OR OFFENDED YOU SOMEHOW...

31:03.061 --> 31:04.196
YOU SHOULD'VE CALLED

31:04.196 --> 31:06.531
AND GIVEN US
A-A CHANCE TO APOLOGIZE.

31:06.531 --> 31:09.601
NO.
YOU DID NOTHING WRONG.

31:09.601 --> 31:12.604
THEN WHY STOP
BEING OUR FRIEND?

31:12.604 --> 31:14.740
BEEN 15 YEARS
SINCE YOU CALLED.

31:14.740 --> 31:16.141
WHY?

31:17.142 --> 31:19.311
IT'S HARD TO EXPLAIN.

31:22.514 --> 31:25.250
DID IT HAVE SOMETHING TO DO
WITH BARRETT'S DEATH?

31:25.250 --> 31:28.987
OH, FOR GOD'S SAKE.
CAN WE PLEASE JUST SAY IT?

31:28.987 --> 31:30.655
OUR SON DIED.

31:30.655 --> 31:32.991
AND YOU DIDN'T KNOW
WHAT TO SAY TO US.

31:32.991 --> 31:34.526
WE WERE OUT OF OUR MINDS
WITH GRIEF,

31:34.526 --> 31:37.262
PROBABLY NOT VERY PLEASANT
TO BE AROUND.

31:37.262 --> 31:39.197
BUT STILL...

31:39.197 --> 31:41.233
YOU SHOULD'VE
REACHED OUT TO US.

31:41.233 --> 31:44.302
THAT'S NOT EXACTLY
WHAT HAPPENED.

31:44.302 --> 31:47.406
NICK HAS SOMETHING
TO SAY TO YOU.

31:49.975 --> 31:51.510
WELL, GET ON WITH IT.

31:51.510 --> 31:53.345
THESE MEANINGFUL GLANCES
HAVE GOTTEN ME

31:53.345 --> 31:54.546
ON THE EDGE OF MY SEAT.

31:54.546 --> 31:56.114
[ CHUCKLES ]

31:56.114 --> 31:59.384
WELL, FOR YOU...
TO REALLY UNDERSTAND,

31:59.384 --> 32:02.654
I-I HAVE TO GO BACK
TO THE BEGINNING.

32:02.654 --> 32:06.658
MY MARRIAGE TO DAHLIA
WAS ALWAYS TROUBLED.

32:06.658 --> 32:08.994
WE WERE AWARE
OF SOME TENSION.

32:08.994 --> 32:11.096
IT WAS MORE THAN THAT.

32:11.096 --> 32:14.232
I HAD TO TRAVEL ALL THE TIME
FOR BUSINESS,

32:14.232 --> 32:16.601
WHICH MADE DAHLIA
VERY UNHAPPY.

32:16.601 --> 32:19.971
SHE SPENT SO MUCH TIME
ALONE IN OUR HOUSE

32:19.971 --> 32:23.074
WITH NO ONE TO TALK TO
BUT OUR MAID.

32:23.074 --> 32:27.479
AND AT SOME POINT,
DAHLIA BEGAN TO REALIZE

32:27.479 --> 32:31.583
THAT OPAL WAS
ACTUALLY IN LOVE WITH HER.

32:31.583 --> 32:37.122
AND SO,
ONE UNEVENTFUL AFTERNOON,

32:37.122 --> 32:41.259
DAHLIA DECIDED
SHE WOULD SEDUCE OPAL.

32:41.259 --> 32:43.595
AND THEN, TO HURT ME,

32:43.595 --> 32:46.298
DAHLIA BEGAN LEAVING CLUES
FOR ME TO FIND

32:46.298 --> 32:49.734
SO I'D KNOW
SHE WAS HAVING AN AFFAIR.

32:49.734 --> 32:51.369
I'M SO SORRY
TO INTERRUPT

32:51.369 --> 32:54.239
THIS REALLY EXTRAORDINARILY
TAWDRY TALE,

32:54.239 --> 32:56.975
BUT...WHAT DOES IT HAVE TO DO
WITH US?

32:56.975 --> 32:59.511
HE'S GETTING TO THAT.

32:59.511 --> 33:03.415
DAHLIA FELT THAT IT WASN'T
ENOUGH FOR ME TO BE JEALOUS.

33:04.749 --> 33:07.652
THAT -- THAT MY HUMILIATION
WOULD NOT BE COMPLETE

33:07.652 --> 33:09.521
UNTIL I KNEW
WHO MY RIVAL WAS,

33:09.521 --> 33:13.158
SO SHE DECIDED TO TELL ME
ON OUR WAY

33:13.158 --> 33:15.293
TO A CHAMBER OF COMMERCE
LUNCHEON

33:15.293 --> 33:19.097
WHERE I WAS GOING TO GET
AN AWARD.

33:19.097 --> 33:22.133
I WAS DRIVING
WHEN IT HAPPENED.

33:22.133 --> 33:25.370
OUT OF THE BLUE, SHE JUST
TURNED TO ME AND SAID --

33:25.370 --> 33:28.507
WAIT A MINUTE.
I REMEMBER THAT LUNCHEON.

33:28.507 --> 33:30.141
WE WERE INVITED
BUT COULDN'T GO

33:30.141 --> 33:33.044
BECAUSE WE WERE CELEBRATING
BARRETT'S BIRTHDAY.

33:38.383 --> 33:40.018
OH, MY GOD.

33:43.088 --> 33:45.657
WE WERE DRIVING
PAST THE PARK

33:45.657 --> 33:49.995
WHEN DAHLIA TURNED TO ME
AND SAID,

33:49.995 --> 33:51.563
"I'M HAVING AN AFFAIR
WITH OPAL."

33:51.563 --> 33:55.267
AND I TOOK MY EYES OFF THE ROAD
FOR ONE SECOND.

33:55.267 --> 33:56.234
[ GASPS ]

33:56.234 --> 33:58.103
[ TIRES SCREECH, THUD ]

34:01.540 --> 34:04.743
IT WAS...AN ACCIDENT.

34:07.512 --> 34:09.414
Evelyn:
[ Voice breaking ] NO.

34:09.414 --> 34:11.249
NO, THIS DOESN'T MAKE
ANY SENSE, THOUGH.

34:11.249 --> 34:14.619
'CAUSE BARRETT WAS HIT BY A CAR
THAT SPED AWAY,

34:14.619 --> 34:17.222
AND THE PEOPLE IN THAT CAR
NEVER EVEN STOPPED

34:17.222 --> 34:20.158
[ Crying ]
TO SEE IF MY SON WAS OKAY,

34:20.158 --> 34:22.661
AND I DO NOT BELIEVE
THAT YOU COULD BE THAT CALLOUS.

34:22.661 --> 34:23.728
I...

34:26.331 --> 34:27.999
TELL THEM
WHAT HAPPENED NEXT.

34:27.999 --> 34:30.235
DAHLIA AND I
WERE IN SHOCK.

34:30.235 --> 34:33.204
WE -- WE DIDN'T KNOW
EXACTLY WHAT HAD HAPPENED,

34:33.204 --> 34:36.408
[ Voice breaking ]
BUT WE WERE SCARED,
AND THE NEXT DAY...

34:36.408 --> 34:39.644
WE LEARNED THAT IT WAS BARRETT
THAT WE HAD HIT

34:39.644 --> 34:41.212
AND THAT HE WAS DEAD.

34:41.212 --> 34:44.449
AND WE WERE DEVASTATED.

34:44.449 --> 34:47.252
[ Crying ] AND DAHLIA WANTED
TO COME TELL YOU.

34:47.252 --> 34:52.991
THEN I WAS AFRAID IT WOULD
RUIN MY CAREER, AND...

34:52.991 --> 34:56.261
AND WE COULDN'T BRING
YOUR LITTLE BOY BACK.

34:56.261 --> 35:02.300
SO I CONVINCED HER
TO SAY NOTHING.

35:02.300 --> 35:04.636
I UNDERSTAND
THIS IS OPENING UP OLD WOUNDS,

35:04.636 --> 35:07.205
BUT I THOUGHT
YOU DESERVED TO KNOW.

35:08.373 --> 35:09.608
ADRIAN.

35:09.608 --> 35:11.676
OH!
ADRIAN!

35:11.676 --> 35:13.144
[ GRUNTS ]

35:13.144 --> 35:14.245
[ GASPS ]

35:14.245 --> 35:15.380
GET UP!
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

35:15.380 --> 35:17.115
YOU KILLED MY SON!

35:17.115 --> 35:18.383
YES, HE DID.

35:18.383 --> 35:21.252
YOU LEFT HIM TO DIE
IN THE STREET!

35:21.252 --> 35:23.154
YES. HE DID.

35:23.154 --> 35:24.522
LOOK AT ME.

35:35.300 --> 35:37.669
MAKE NO MISTAKE.

35:37.669 --> 35:39.971
THE ONLY REASON
THAT YOU ARE NOT DEAD RIGHT NOW

35:39.971 --> 35:42.273
IS I BELIEVE A HARSHER
PUNISHMENT AWAITS YOU --

35:42.273 --> 35:46.111
ONE...
BEYOND YOUR IMAGINATION.

35:51.416 --> 35:54.386
I WANT HIM
TAKEN TO THE POLICE.

35:54.386 --> 35:55.654
THAT'S OUR NEXT STOP.

36:05.030 --> 36:08.133
FOR WHAT IT'S WORTH...

36:08.133 --> 36:12.504
I AM SO...VERY SORRY.

36:12.504 --> 36:16.641
AFTER ALL THESE YEARS...

36:16.641 --> 36:20.478
IT'S WORTH
NOTHING AT ALL.

36:26.184 --> 36:27.485
[ SIGHS SHAKILY ]

36:39.297 --> 36:41.533
[ INHALES SHARPLY ]

36:41.533 --> 36:44.369
ALL THESE YEARS, I BLAMED YOU
FOR BARRETT'S DEATH.

36:44.369 --> 36:46.571
[ SNIFFLES ]

36:46.571 --> 36:49.407
GOD,
WHAT DID I DO TO YOU?

36:49.407 --> 36:52.243
TO US?

36:52.243 --> 36:53.645
[ SIGHS ]

36:53.645 --> 36:55.680
CAN YOU EVER
FORGIVE ME?

37:00.652 --> 37:04.656
[ Voice breaking ] I THINK
IT'S TIME WE FORGIVE EACH OTHER.

37:04.656 --> 37:08.226
[ SNIFFLES, SIGHS ]

37:08.226 --> 37:11.229
FOR EVERYTHING.

37:22.640 --> 37:24.342
[ WOMEN GASP ]

37:24.342 --> 37:27.278
THAT'S
A BEAUTIFUL BRIDE.

37:27.278 --> 37:29.180
ABSOLUTELY GORGEOUS!

37:29.180 --> 37:30.715
OH, ROSIE.

37:30.715 --> 37:32.283
HOW DO YOU FEEL?

37:32.283 --> 37:34.552
I'M OKAY.

37:34.552 --> 37:36.521
IS SOMETHING WRONG?

37:36.521 --> 37:37.589
MAYBE.

37:37.589 --> 37:39.457
I DON'T KNOW.

37:39.457 --> 37:41.426
ARE YOU HUNGRY?
I GOT MINTS IN MY PURSE.

37:41.426 --> 37:42.727
I'M FINE.

37:42.727 --> 37:46.064
I JUST DON'T KNOW
IF I SHOULD MARRY SPENCE.

37:46.064 --> 37:47.165
ROSIE!

37:47.165 --> 37:48.733
IT'S OKAY.

37:48.733 --> 37:51.636
IT'S NATURAL FOR THE BRIDE TO BE
NERVOUS ON HER WEDDING DAY.

37:51.636 --> 37:53.605
I'M NOT NERVOUS.

37:53.605 --> 37:54.973
WHAT HAPPENED?

37:54.973 --> 37:56.541
SPENCE AND I HAD A FIGHT.

37:56.541 --> 37:58.676
ABOUT WHAT?
MONEY.

37:58.676 --> 38:01.613
HE DOESN'T HAVE A JOB,
BUT HE KEEPS SPENDING.

38:01.613 --> 38:05.683
I TRIED TO TELL HIM
WE NEED TO BE CAREFUL.

38:05.683 --> 38:07.719
HE WOULDN'T LISTEN.

38:07.719 --> 38:14.692
I FELT LIKE I WAS SEEING HIM
FOR THE FIRST TIME.

38:14.692 --> 38:16.361
HE'S A CHILD.

38:16.361 --> 38:17.762
THAT IS NOT TRUE.

38:17.762 --> 38:20.031
IT <i>IS.</i>

38:20.031 --> 38:22.634
HE DOES NOT KNOW
WHAT IT MEANS TO BE POOR.

38:22.634 --> 38:26.571
ERNESTO WAS SO CAREFUL
WITH HIS MONEY.

38:26.571 --> 38:28.006
HONEY.

38:28.006 --> 38:29.207
YOU SHOULD NEVER COMPARE

38:29.207 --> 38:31.176
YOUR SECOND HUSBAND
TO YOUR FIRST.

38:31.176 --> 38:33.344
I CAN'T HELP IT.

38:33.344 --> 38:38.149
WE WERE SO HAPPY, RIGHT UP
UNTIL THE DAY HE WAS MURDERED.

38:38.149 --> 38:42.720
I DON'T KNOW IF I WILL BE
AS HAPPY WITH SPENCE.

38:42.720 --> 38:46.491
LOOK, BEING MARRIED TO SPENCE
WILL BE DIFFERENT,

38:46.491 --> 38:49.561
BUT THAT DOESN'T MEAN
IT CAN'T BE JUST AS WONDERFUL.

38:49.561 --> 38:51.129
OH,
I KNOW IT <i>WILL</i> BE,

38:51.129 --> 38:54.032
BECAUSE SPENCE LOVES YOU
WITH ALL HIS HEART.

38:54.032 --> 38:56.000
Carmen:
WE SEE IT IN HIS EYES, ROSIE.

38:56.000 --> 38:58.036
IT MAKES US
CRAZY JEALOUS OF YOU.

38:58.036 --> 38:59.070
[ LAUGHTER ]

38:59.070 --> 39:00.505
REALLY?

39:00.505 --> 39:01.973
YEAH.
YEAH.

39:01.973 --> 39:03.508
SO, DON'T WORRY
ABOUT THE FUTURE.

39:03.508 --> 39:05.543
HAVE FAITH
THAT SOME PEOPLE DO GET TO LIVE

39:05.543 --> 39:07.378
HAPPILY EVER AFTER.

39:10.048 --> 39:12.283
THANK YOU.

39:40.378 --> 39:43.147
HI, MAMI.
HOW'S ROSIE?

39:43.147 --> 39:45.149
JUST WEDDING-DAY JITTERS,
BUT SHE'LL BE FINE.

39:45.149 --> 39:46.451
DID YOU GET SEATS
FOR US?

39:46.451 --> 39:48.419
RIGHT UP FRONT.
REMI'S HOLDING THEM FOR US.

39:48.419 --> 39:50.021
[ CELLPHONE RINGING ]
OH.

39:50.021 --> 39:52.156
GO AHEAD.
I'LL CATCH UP.

39:52.156 --> 39:53.458
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

39:53.458 --> 39:55.093
HELLO?

39:55.093 --> 39:58.029
Ms. Diaz, it's Dr. Kimball
from Doheny Medical Center.

39:58.029 --> 39:59.564
HI. YOUR NURSE
ALREADY CALLED.

39:59.564 --> 40:01.332
SHE SAID I WASN'T A MATCH
FOR GENEVIEVE.

40:01.332 --> 40:04.369
I know, but when we tested you
for a kidney donation,

40:04.369 --> 40:06.671
we also ran
a basic blood panel.

40:06.671 --> 40:09.040
OKAY.
IS SOMETHING WRONG?

40:09.040 --> 40:10.541
No.

40:10.541 --> 40:13.544
I just thought you might want
to know -- you're pregnant.

40:13.544 --> 40:15.413
[ SLOW-TEMPO PIANO PLAYING ]

40:18.216 --> 40:22.587
♪ BEAUTIFUL DREAMER ♪

40:22.587 --> 40:27.058
♪ WAKE UNTO ME ♪

40:27.058 --> 40:32.430
♪ STARLIGHT AND DEWDROPS
ARE WAITING FOR THEE ♪

40:34.465 --> 40:42.173
♪ SOUNDS OF THE RUDE WORLD
HEARD IN THE DAY ♪

40:42.173 --> 40:48.980
♪ LULLED BY THE MOONLIGHT
HAVE ALL PASSED AWAY ♪

40:48.980 --> 40:52.717
♪ BEAUTIFUL DREAMER ♪

